
[1]negligence

   NEGLIGENCE, n.

   1. Neglect; omission to do; more generally,

   2. Habitual omission of that which ought to be done, or a habit of
   omitting to do things, either from carelessness or design. Negligence
   is usually the child of sloth or laziness, and the parent of disorders
   in business, often of poverty.
